<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="88" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="25.[224,1207,2200,2746]" pageId="25" pageNumber="88">Definition. Shell minute, thin, globular fusiform with round base. Protoconch deviated with final whorl embracing much of earlier whorl ornament of fine collabral threads; aperture large with strong columellar siphonal fold.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[273,886,2476,2516]" pageId="25" pageNumber="88" type="multiple">
<paragraph blockId="25.[224,1207,2200,2746]" box="[273,886,2476,2516]" pageId="25" pageNumber="88">Geological age. Late Tournaisian.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="88" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[224,1207,2200,2746]" pageId="25" pageNumber="88">
Remarks. No existing genus can be compared with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[225,531,2570,2609]" class="Gastropoda" family="Soleniscidae" genus="Globobulimorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coenogastropoda incertae sedis" pageId="25" pageNumber="120" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Globobulimorpha</taxonomicName>
. The protoconch of the genus is deviated, but it is not clearly seen as heterostrophic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
